						<p>Tried, at one point, when was younger and couldn't be arsed to "book-larnin'", with 32. You get measurably ~worse~ timing, because not only is thermal drift -- your chief enemy -- common to all of the "N chickens", but you've also now built a multiheaded antenna to pick up Johnson noise and any stray RF (the portion of which which comes from the resonators themselves, you cannot shield away.)</p>
<p>The idea is an elementary "из говна пулю не слепишь" fail.</p>
						</li>

